               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18750920-name-46" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18750920-name-46" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18750920-name-46" type="surname" value="FIELDER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18750920-name-46" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN FIELDER</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the Bird in Hand, London Road, Bromley—on 23rd August, about 9.45, I was in the bar parlour and the barmaid brought me a shilling—I said that it was bad, gave it back to her, went into the bar and found sharp there (<hi rend="italic">see next case</hi>)—he said to him "This shilling is bad"—he said "I beg pardon, I am sorry," and tendered a good sixpence—the bad shilling was returned to him and he went away—I went outside and saw him join a man darkly dressed, but I do not recognise the prisoner—I pointed them out to Basson.</p>
